pedigree vs. filigree . filigree wins . period dramas are , by definition , delicate commodities : they 're balanced on that , ahem , `` razor 's edge '' between high brow and just plain fussiness . i think `` howard 's end '' is a case of a robust novel buried in tea time and english lace . milliners , set designers and helena bonham carter 's hair stylist had their job cut out for them on this one